Reasoning: The paper deals with a variant of the near neighbor problem, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of computational geometry and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses LSH-based algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and data mining applications, and hence it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves probability and randomness, which are important concepts in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR).
